caption: Always great, employees are always friendly and helpful.
Does not disappoint! I’ve been here twice for the quarter burger and it’s sooo good! Make sure you ask for truffle fries cooked to perfection. I’ll probably get it a third time

Took advantage of the Brunch Deal on PulsD.  Had the Burger with Handcut Fries while my foodie partner in crime had the Fried Oysters and Eggs.  Food cooked to perfection, drinks were good, staff courteous, atmosphere chill.  Wil come again.
The biscuits were the BEST. Ask the bartender to make a Mojito mocktail...you won't be disappointed.

It was my first time dining at The Quarter and I enjoyed my experience. We made reservations so we had no issue getting seated. You have the option for a paper menu or to scan a QR code on your phone (great for covid protocols).  The food was great - we all ordered from the brunch menu. I do feel that the food took a pretty long time considering it was just eggs but that's not a big issue. They did mess up one order slightly but nothing to complain about! Food was good and I enjoyed my first time there.
I always come by buying some food in here. I like the swift customer service and well made dishes. Fantastic work.
Great spot for both happy hour and brunch. Delicious cocktails and food. Check the brussel sprouts, watermelon mojito, spicy marg! Garden was warm and safe.
Got seated outside and no one came to serve us. Left after waiting 20 minutes. Would give negative stars if possible
Good food and good backyard heated space.

Quarter burger was great. Fries were solid. Eggs Benedict w the basil hollandaise was no bueno unless you’re on a health craze and love mushrooms and kale with your eggs Benny. I say, why fix something that’s not broken.  Service was subpar for only having three parties to serve. It was cold af out back and the heater was broken.

Came here for a brunch lunch, burger looked good but was not cooked to order and dry, flavorless. Coffee was half full and overpriced, service wasn’t any better unfortunately. Maybe was a bad day? Not bothering to check here again
I really love their food. I always get good service there. The place is well kept and the employees are always helpful. Keep up the good work.

The service was great. The area outside was cozy and warm. The food was delicious. The brunch burger called the Quarter Burger was cooked to perfection and the French fries were delicious. Coffee was very good too. Highly recommend. Give them a shot.
Kinda cold in the outside so wear a sweater but overall ambience experience so nice
The Quarter Brooklyn was a great experience!! The ambiance is very welcoming. Amazing food and service. Staff made great recommendations.... definitely coming back for the *Chilaquiles ! 👌🏽
It was a great experience and I really enjoyed the meals.
The mezcal mango margarita and calamari is really good and the bartender is nice and friendly. He gave us an awesome service.

Drinks were watery and didn’t come with any of the garnishes listed on the menu. My brother nearly chipped his tooth on a piece of shell that  was stuck in a fried oyster and when I brought it to the waiter’s attention, he snapped that he was just the bartender and couldn’t do anything about it except tell the kitchen staff. He was also slamming our drinks and plates down on the table and never offered us condiments or anything else. We left as quickly as we could because we were so uncomfortable. I understand that they may have been understaffed, but that’s no reason to yell at customers. Never coming back.
Really excellent brunch food and drinks. Quick service and kitchen. Lovely back patio with heat lamps + fresh air for relaxed, safe outdoor dining.
Great drinks, appetizers, atmosphere & service ! Best calamari / fritto misto I've had outside of Italy or Portugal. Yummy drink specials. Stunning outdoor garden patio. Jovial staff.

It was great to finally be able to grab a bite outside of your own house. nice place, fairly empty due to current situation but service was friendly and I felt well taken care of. social distancing was well kept too with enough supplies to stay sanitized and safe. food and drinks were absolutely fine too, maybe a bit over priced🤔😳 overall, I do recommend "The Quarter" - if you decide to risk it and change the scenery once in awhile.
Big fan of their burgers here and would recommend you try this place out if you haven't. And they have a great menu selection too.
Stylish and cosy place. Recommend for brunch.
Nice spot for a pre-theater dinner near BAM.
Nice brunch menu
Solid brunch place.  Good oysters.
Amazing restaurant and awesome, friendly staff!

Speechless!!! We have seated in patio for brunch for party of 6 with my girls.Everything was great as we expected. You must try the Smoky Maria based in bloody marry. We all got different brunch dishes and loved every item we ordered. Fresh baked home made biscuits!!! Must try. The manager (who served us as well) did a great job even the place was slammed. Attentive and very polite!!. We will definitely go back soon.

Haven’t been in town for a while and this was the first time I found The Quarter Restaurant. My parents and I were heading to show in BAM and made a reservation over the phone. The Manager reserved a table as we expected since my Mom having trouble with hearing. We tried feta stuffed dates as appetizer and followed With Mussels,Burger and Salmon as entrees. Nothing wrong with the taste but the food could have server in a better presentation. We did enjoy our drinks,food and desserts as well as very friendly,helpful service with a great attitude. Thank you again

We tried this place yesterday, for the first time and it was awesome, overall experience was PERFECT!!! We can’t wait to go back and we will be back soon. Food is super fresh and delicious. Drinks are fresh and nicely prepared! Oysters are perfect! Seafood is very fresh and delicious. Steaks, burgers and pasta prepared just like we requested. Great presentation! Friendly staff and very comfortable atmosphere inside. Result = PERFECT! People you should try this place!!! Satisfaction Guaranteed!
Loved our apps, drinks, and dinner. Looking forward to visiting again!
Drinks were terrible and food was okay.
Really good food and service.
Cozy, tasty and relaxed
Great restaurant and really friendly staff.
Great location, very nice service and so yummy dessert!
Food and service were not as good as you'd expect from a fairly expensive place.
Great service!! Excellent steak!!
Service ok really didn't care for the steak

The space is amazing and the food was really good. Get the fries! I loved the patio but beware of sitting in the back. They may forget you. We showed up when there were only a few tables full and received spotty service. I wanted to order a drink and biscuts before the rest of our party arrived but we were not waited on for about 10 minutes after being seated. By the time a server got around to us, I gave up. We watched the wait staff be incredibly attentive to the tables around us, but we had to flag them down. The brunch menu has great options but there was no bottomless drink option. My party found the drink prices on the high side for brunch but would have expected them if it was dinner service.
Seated us at the table outside. Never returned with water or to ask our orders. Incredibly rude. Ended up going somewhere else
Very nice atmosphere and great food for the price - excellent value for a place near BAM.
Great drinks and AMAZING food! The atmosphere is beautiful and reflects the evolving neighborhood

Pleasantly surprised.  It's sort of a hidden gem in the middle of no where. 1 block from the station.  Oysters are great, quality kind.  Not sure why anyone would miss out on the experience.  Staff is super formal.  Guests and customers are just the right type.  Please look good when dress up because easily this place could be considered high class. Just want to give everyone a heads up.  You will not be disappointed.  And if you are disappointed,  the staff will dip what they can to make sure you are happy.  Just saying.

Came here with my family for brunch. The menu is kind of small, but the dishes are pretty good. The back patio is really the star of the show and I hear their oyster happy hour is a good deal if you're into that.
Excellent oysters and good price. The dressing on the pasta was very tasty. Good spot for dating.
Good food and good drink selection

The food is amazing, the seasonal watermelon drinks are good and the outdoor seating is a must.  My wife and I chose a variety of appetizers from the menu.  The feta stuffed dates are beyond delicious.  Their mini fish tacos are the right level of spice.  We wished we had tried the fried calamari.  My daughter had the fish and chips and the fish had a wonderful light batter - which she prefers.  My son devoured the hamburger.  To top it off, we highly recommend the apple pie crumble.  The staff was very attentive and we were well taken care of from start to finish.

Amazing experience.  Everything we ordered was extremely well presented and taste delicious.  Recommend the Oysters and Mussels and plenty of options for those veggies.  The manager was great and helped curate a perfect meal.

Solid food and nice staff. A bit disappointed that I had a reservation and even called ahead of time to let them know we were running about 10 min late...yet they seemed really confused when we arrived. Luckily there was one table available, so no issues. The food was tasty...nothing spectacular, but I'd to try more.
Not bad for a quick bite

We spent a really nice time there. Good food, nice wines.. And specially the waitress was really kind with An excepcional care about if we were enjoying the meal and giving us good recomendations. I recommend 100%
Great service and food
Got hurried out the door because "there is a big reservation and we need your table". Food was decent. Drinks sub-par.

The Quarter has great food and absolutely fantastic drinks. I highly recommend going here for any occasion. The vibe is cozy, the staff are more than hospitable, and the food is freaking good. Highly recommend the Fish Tacos and the Shishito Peppers. I've yet to find any better Shishito Peppers!

Great food, Great drinks, mixologists make amazing cocktails AND mock tails! I reccomend the general tso mini buns, stuffed dates, amd the burger or the chicken sandwiches!!!!!! (I've been four times, very uncommon for me)

The food was fantastic but i was served spoiled orange juice and they did not even apologize. They gave me a replacement drink but this really soured my appetite. I had the pasta and loved it, and the food deserves 5 stars, but the juice ruined things.
Great oysters, and the salmon dish was amazingly fabulous. Will be back.
Oysters were great. Our entrees (mussels, salmon) were sub-par. Service also left a lot to be desired.

The hubby and I had a fantastic experience last night at The Quarter, we've walked by this place so many times. We always thought it was a basement bar, but do not let that deceive you - this is an excellent and quaint restaurant.  The food was outstanding, we had oysters with butter/ginger sauce... and they were out of this world. Oh the burger, I would try to describe it but I fear drooling on my keyboard.  Mostly it was the service that impressed us, they were super friendly and attentive. We felt at home and comfortable the entire time. Truly, if you're in Fort Greene you need to check this place out. <dools on keyboard>
Burger was excellent. Brussel sprouts excellent. Chicken sandwich I wouldn't order again to be honest. Cocktails were solid. 10/10 service.
My go to in Fort Greene for good seafood dishes and dollar oysters! Love the outside patio.
It's hard to tell which is better. The service or the food. Go for both!
Good Eats, Great Atmosphere... blood orange gimlet.. no food tonight but, I do recommend the homemade cavatelli pasta..

I’ve only been to this Fort Greene restaurant for Sunday brunch, which lasts from opening at 10 a.m. until 4 p.m. The enclosed patio is great for groups and comfortable year-round with throw blankets and adjustable space heaters. The menu is delicious and servers were very friendly, remembering and welcoming us back on our second visit. Eggs on Brussels sprouts are perfectly poached. Beverages from spicy Bloody Marys to rich espresso drinks are made to order. Their hand-cut French fries are thick and crispy. Reservations are accepted via Open Table.
Try to sit on the enclosed back patio!

It is a small cozy place and it was a wonderful surprise. The oysters were surprisingly tasteful and they sure do a mean burger. The service was great too, we were sited right away, even thought it was packed. I can't wait to come back!
Solid basic brunch spot, generally not as crowded as other options in the neighborhood. Nice Bloody Mary recipe.

A relaxing place with phenomenal atmosphere, friendly staff, great food. The place was slammed, and they still were very attentive to get us seats quickly. We will definitely back to try more food and desserts.
$1 oyster happy, good service, nice atmosphere, intimate. Good calamari and lamb tacos
Great place to work and have a good meal.
Great atmosphere! Great good
Great food,contemporary cocktails,wide wariety of wine selections and friendly service.....

I stumbled in here for brunch after my original destination was closed. The menu was eclectic but pretty much covered anything you would want for brunch. The chilequiles were great and spicy and filling and the Benedict was huge and delicious. The service was prompt but we didn't feel rushed. All of this and the entrees were only $13 in NYC. I would certainly come back.
Great service they are super amazing worker and delicious food I like to give them 7 start not just 5
Delicious food, a bit crowded, but decent atmosphere

Yesterday was my Birthday! Went to the The Quarter with my best friend to celebrate. I was soo pleased with the service we received. The food, the ambiance and the help was excellent. I left the place feeling overjoyed. Soo happy that I spent my special day there and will highly recommend this lovely place to all of my friends and can hardly wait to go back. Made such a beautiful memory there 🥰.
Love this place! Always $1 oysters, can’t beat that! Good food, tastes home made, attentive service. I live a couple neighborhoods over, but always try to make it here once in a while.

Food and cocktail were good but service was inconsistent at best. We were sat in the corner and consistently ignored. Our origin server never returned to our table and we were left without water multiple times while other tables glasses were refilled. When we were finally able to wave down a server she filled half of the tables glasses and never returned. We also had to flag down a server to give us and pick up our check.
It was a wonderful ambiance tasty food friendly and profesional staf
Great little place when you find it, I walked by this place for two years and never realized how nice a place it is, Great food friendly staff and nice ambiance.
Good food good service. Enjoyed their burger and will return.
Had my 50th birthday dinner here. Lovely ambience...

Gotta say this place caught me by surprise, in a good way! Entrance is pretty unassuming and kinda pub-like but the restaurant is very charming and cozy inside. Went for brunch and got the Bloody Maria and Chilaquiles. Both were delicious!! Staff were very attentive and friendly. Will definitely return to explore the menu further.

Decent place. Had the Charcuterie and that was just ok, hence only 3 stars. However, will be back for the burger as that looked amazing.  Went back and wanted to provide an update. Had the burger and it was amazing. Also had the dates appetizer and they matched the burger. Plus the wine they served us was superb  (don't remember the name but us the wine they feature).  So upped them to 4 stars. And will return!

A little pricey, but they have a happy hour. It’s got a great atmosphere, the staff is very friendly, and the drinks are great.

I stopped in for brunch at 10:30 Sunday and initially was the only person there, but groups began drifting in quickly. I had the home fries, which were fine but needed salt, and the lentil soup. Although the menu just said "lentil," it was a red lentil soup - pureed smooth and bursting with complex flavor. The toasted bread was a great accompaniment. I liked it so much I ordered another to go! Decor is cute, service was good - I will be back.

This was my second time at The Quarter. First time was a few months ago when we went for brunch with friends and had a lovely time. This time went on a date with my boyfriend and we loved it. Stuff is always very friendly and the food is delicious. We will definitely go back either with friends or on another romantic date
food ok, service could be better
Great food and cocktails. Loved dollar osyter everyday. Garden in the back is a gem. Will be back for sure. Highly recommended.
The food and cocktails were great!! And I just found out that they will be opening for lunch! So excited! Lovely garden too
Nice decor, can accommodate groups, but the food tasted bland.
Excellent food and atmosphere. Wife and I stumbled upon this place tonight and very glad we did. We recommend.

Oh the pancakes are amazing!!!!!!

Enjoyed my visit to the Quarter! They have a fun cocktail menu with lots of interesting drinks. The food was delicious too. Definitely sit in the little open air section in the back.
The quality of the food was just alright. The fries were rock hard, the sauce for the moules a bit salty. Others in the party had decent entrees, but for the price, in NYC you can do a lot better.
Great service , great food , fantastic atmosphere
Food and drinks were amazing. Everyone who works here is kind and accommodating. The backyard is a great for a nice day, and the inside is dim and romantic. Very peaceful.
sat in the back patio, was nice. Food was quick but check was not. had the brussel sprouts for brunch, very good food!
Good place to bring your parents to eat. been going here for years.

Came in for a late night dessert. The waiter was kind enough to oblige even though it was like 30 minutes until closing and they already closed down the kitchen. We'd told them we'd be fast and we were.
Nice surrounding tucked away, try out the back in summertime
Always procative great theater.  Not everything this season was gold but I will always subscribe.
Nice li'l bar & restaurant. Beautifully set outdoor canopy seating area in the back. Interesting & Delicious brunch menu!

The worst food in NYC. One star for the garden, bartender was nice, cocktails were decent. Can’t believe this place can get away with the food that they serve. Ordered five plates to share and all five were HORRIBLE absolutely no flavor. Really tried to give it the benefit of a doubt but couldn’t. Steak was cold and raw when ordered medium. Would not want to try the oysters due to how the rest of our food was prepared. Hoping this will save someone else from spending $70 on a few bites of food.

This is an amazing restaurant, it is next to none my wife loves it as well. The food is amazing and everytime we go I have at least have 60 to100 oysters. My pic will be on the wall soon😎. My wife and I love the quater.....las th but not least the owner and all of the workers are professional and great people that make us feel at home.
Good food, good service, romantic atmosphere

Fantastic vibe here! The main area is a charming mix, equal parts bar and restaurant; and the back patio is a lovely escape yet still protected from the rain. There's a great variety of drinks as well as desserts. Service was helpful but occassionally needed a nudge (which I appreciated, as opposed to me being prodded by them).
I was here for a private party apps were fantastic, and drinks were made very well. Friendly staff.
Friendly staff and beautiful decor
Great covered and uncovered garden
Love the backyard! Chill brunch & staff is friendly. The buratta is incredible! Will be back to try more items!

Oysters were good but our drinks and the rest of the food was very underwhelming considering the cost. Beautiful restaurant with a great outdoor space but outside of the oysters would order anything else.
Spicy fried chicken is spicy to the point of not tasting anything
Intimate, great vibe, food ok, great drinks.

Great small plates and oysters. Had a great date night!
Dollar oysters, great cocktail specials and cool staff. Checkout the new revamped backyard.
Very delicious oysters, charcuterie plate and drinks.

Love this place. Beautiful bar. Delicous food. Lovely backyard garden. Close to BAM.
Food is good but while we were chatting, and because we were no longer consuming, they asked us to leave. Politely and all but it is still rude.
Okish. Not special.

This is definitely the place to go have cocktails and amazing food in Fort Greene. The salmon is my favorite with the blood orange gimlet it is pure bliss! The service is always perfection, great energy, good music it is definitely a gem of the Fort Greene community. Love this place!

I had the most incredible experience here. I stumbled in with a friend on a random Monday and I'm so glad we did! Our bartender was exceptional and our cocktails were ahhmazimg! The place had such a cozy vibe. The staff were really accommodating and friendly. For dinner, I had the lentil soup which was fantastic but my favorite was the Salmon dish... to die for ! We were so full that we didn't have room for dessert but im definitely going back to explore more of the menu. My new fav spot in Fort Greene! Glad we wandered in and will definitely be coming back soon!!
Comfortable, Tasty food, Good drinks
Came here for breakfast/brunch and had the French toast.  It was good, and the outdoor seating area is pleasant.  It also has a covering in case the weather isn't cooperating.
The burger with mushroom and truffle mayo was amazing, but lost a star because the drinks from the cocktail menu weren't very good, considering the price.
Outdoor space is so cute and food was amazing. Had a birthday and let us bring in our own cookies for dessert. Highly recommended.
Wow! just ordered a burger and the caramelized brussel sprouts w/parmesean.  Simply amazing!  I'll be back. -. Came back.  Amazing!!!  Oysterville

Delicious seafood! Great oyster selection!
service was ok.
Amazing food, great service by Fatih the manager!!
Yummy is all I can say. Try the bbq lamb tacos

Great date spot. Excellent food and service. Wasn't crazy busy on a Saturday night but I have a feeling it won't stay that way for long. Go here.

Love this place. There is a shiny silver ceiling, and the light bounces off it just so. It's very nice. Really sets the mood. The cocktails are too kill for, there is one that tastes just like a campfire (sounds strange but v good). If you have to try just one thing I'd recommend the risotto. Oh. Baby.
I enjoyed dining at this restaurant. The grilled branzino was incredible. Their wine list is superb. I've been there several times, and each time I leave feeling very satisfied.

SHAME ON YOU!!  WHO RIPS OFF HIGH SCHOOL TEACHERS?  We - about 30 high school English teachers - reserved The Quarter for our holiday party. This was the contract: $35.00 per person includes food, space, tax and tip Food: Rolling & ongoing food of: Calamari, Fish Tacos, Steakhouse Toasts, Eggplant Toasts,  Tossed or Caesar Salad, and main dishes of Chicken Franchaise and Mussels with Frites,  They will keep the food coming!  We will have a sectioned off space towards the back where the garden is.  What we got was... teeny plates of the finger food that were not replenished until one of us had to find a waiter and ask. Every. Time. And that's it.  NO main dishes. We waited and waited, asked and asked. They said they were working on it.  Never happened. NEVER FULFILLED THEIR PART OF THE DEAL.  OH... we also got a big surprise: We were approached with bill for almost THREE HUNDRED ADDITIONAL DOLLARS for gratuity and use of space and something that we still don't understand.  THEY SERIOUSLY HONESTY MADE IT UP ON THE SPOT!  AND THEY GOT REALLY REALLY NASTY ABOUT IT.  It was unprofessional. It was unBrooklyn. It was ugly.
The feta stuffed dates, and endive salad were amazing. Great oyster prices, and friendly bartender.

Stuffed figs with feta wrapped in bacon: burnt; roasted cauliflower: not memorable but was all eaten by the table; Brussel sprouts: amazing, could have eaten a few more rounds - resisted with sprinkled Romano cheese; steak: just another one:: service really nice and fun

Finally got to try this cozy spot around the corner, and will definitely be back! First we were greeted by the nicest guy,  so major points for service. It was that type of personable and friendly service that already made us enjoy the place as soon as we sat down.  We ordered the $1 oysters, fish tacos, and the general tso's bun- a food with a fusion and so much flavor! All highly recommended! The drinks were amazing, from the wine, cocktail, to the Turkish beer.  The place was cozy, romantic, and had a relaxing vibe. The music fit the place perfect. Also not too loud , which is great if you want to go there on a date or have a conversation with friends. Also- beautiful decor, and for warmer days- a garden! 🙌🏻
Great addition to the neighborhood. Friendly service and sizeable backyard. Cocktails are solid, especially fresh watermelon juice margarita.

Went for the $1 oysters on weekdays which weren't good quality. Ordered the burrata (good but not the best quality cheese), calamari (fantastic) and fish tacos (excellent). There's a mescal cocktail with cilantro which I would also recommend.

We love to walk around our neighborhood and try out new restaurants. We stumbled upon The Quarter and are so glad we did!!! Great food, delicious cocktails and awesome team. With the summer around the corner, I can't wait to go back and sit out in the patio!
My new top spot in BK. Funny & friendly staff! See you om my bday!

Great vibes, beautiful atmosphere and friendly staff. So happy Forth Green has a spot like this. Their cocktails are very refreshing. I'm already a regular and I heard they will be soon open for lunch. Can't wait!
Such a nice spot! We sat outside for dinner and enjoyed our time so much. Loved the music and decor. The staff are all on point! I already booked another reservation for brunch

The food was amazing!!!!! You also get warm complimentary bread, the staff was really friendly, nice setting for a romantic dinner, the restaurant wasn't too loud where you had to scream at each other, and the pricing was not bad at all.  Excellent wine selection with good prices, dessert was a light tasty end as it should be -
The best cocktails you can ever have! The food is very tasty and I absolutely love the atmosphere.
Great atmosphere, fantastic food, and excellent service. I'll be going back often, especially to enjoy that back patio as the weather gets nicer.
Great staff, drinks, food and vibe. I'd love to get a little more for my dollar, but the quality is so high I forgive them.
